Uses of Package
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.data

Packages that use de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.data
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.bytecode Provides the classes for byte code instructions. 
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.general Provides abstract superclasses for the instruction classes. 
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.data Provides interfaces for marking the behaviour of instructions with regard to the datal-flow. 
de.wwu.muggl.instructions.replaced.replacer Provides ReplacingInstruction classes that can be used to set QuickInstruction classes. 
 

Classes in de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.data used by de.wwu.muggl.instructions.bytecode
OtherFrameStackPush
          The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of another but the currently executed frame.
StackPop
          The implementing instruction is known to pop at least one element from the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
StackPush
          The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
VariableDefining
          The implementing instruction is known to define a variable in the sense of data-flow tracking.
VariableLoading
          The implementing instruction is known to load a variable in the sense of data-flow tracking.
VariableUsing
          The implementing instruction is known to use a variable in the sense of data-flow tracking.Please note that the wide instruction will not be marked by this interface, even though it (among others) provides widened access to store.
VariablyStackPop
          The implementing instruction is known to pop at least one element from the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
VariablyStackPush
          The implementing instruction is known to push an element onto the operand stack of the currently executed frame.
